DIGEST
SB 394 Original 2026 Regular Session Edmonds
Present law provides for the Louisiana Giving All True Opportunity to Rise (LA GATOR)
Scholarship Program, which is a state-funded Education Scholarship Account (ESA)
program, that provides eligible families with state funds to pay for private school tuition at
a BESE approved nonpublic school, tutoring, textbooks, and other educational expenses.
Present law provides that the La. Dept. of Education may hire a program manager (private
vendor) to administer and manage the day-to-day operations of the LA GATOR scholarship
program and to ensure accountability with state law.
Present law provides that the La. Dept. of Education will allocate scholarship funds to each
student's account, on quarterly basis, in order for the student's parent to pay for educational
expenses. Present law further provides that participating nonpublic schools are to be paid
quarterly for student tuition for students that attend an approved nonpublic school.
Present law provides for student privacy rights which prohibit the sharing of the personally
identifiable information of students, without written parental consent. Present law also
prohibits data collection of students' personal information, mandates secure data storage,
prohibits using student data for marketing, and imposes penalties for violations. Present law
limits personal student information from being given to a private company or vendor, even
if the company is a vendor for an educational agency.
Proposed law retains present law and provides for a voluntary limited student privacy waiver
option for a parent whose child enrolls full-time in a participating nonpublic school, in order
to expedite payment of the student's tuition. Proposed law defines "participating nonpublic
school" to mean a BESE approved nonpublic school that enrolls students who are approved
for LA GATOR scholarships.
