Proposed law provides for the voluntary limited student privacy waiver to serve as a
mechanism to reserve spots in participating nonpublic schools, ensure timely tuition
payments, and prevent loss of enrollment due to payment delays, while limiting the
disclosure of all of other student privacy information that is not related to the expedited
payments of full-time tuition.
Proposed law provides that the voluntary, limited, student privacy waiver option for parents
whose child enrolls full-time in a participating nonpublic school so that the La. Dept. of
Education can share the following private information with both the LA GATOR program
manager (private company and vendor) and the participating nonpublic school, as follows:
(1) Student name and ID number.
(2) Date of birth.
(3) Grade level.
(4) Parent contact information.
(5) Enrollment and scholarship eligibility status.
Proposed law provides that the program managers (private company or vendor) and the
participating schools must only use the student information for scholarship administration
and must implement security safeguards and be contractually prohibited from unauthorized
redisclosure of student information.
Proposed law provides that voluntary limited student privacy waiver, for purposes of
proposed law, remains effective only for the duration of LA GATOR program participation,
unless revoked sooner by the parent.
Effective upon signature of the governor or lapse of time for gubernatorial action.
